decks.notes: This deck focuses on using Allosaurus Rider and Neoform to quickly bring out powerful creatures like Griselbrand, Xenagos, God of Revels, and Ghalta, Stampede Tyrant. It utilizes Eldritch Evolution and Generous Ent to search for key creatures and combo pieces. With the support of Veil of Summer and Pact of Negation to protect its combo, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with big creatures and generate massive amounts of mana with cards like Planar Genesis and Bridgeworks Battle. The inclusion of Atraxa, Grand Unifier provides additional synergy and support for the deck's overall strategy.

The deck focuses on disrupting the opponent with cards like Thoughtseize, Teferi, Time Raveler, and Path to Exile while establishing a board presence with aggressive creatures like Emperor of Bones and Overlord of the Balemurk. The deck also utilizes flicker effects with Ephemerate and Flickerwisp to generate value and protect key creatures. The mana base includes a mix of fetchlands and shocklands to ensure consistent color access. Overall, the deck aims to apply pressure early and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure a win.

The main concept of this deck is to disrupt your opponent's game plan by utilizing cards that tax their resources and slow down their strategy. By combining aggressive creatures with disruptive spells like "Wrath of the Skies" and "Prismatic Ending", the deck aims to control the pace of the game and outvalue the opponent. Cards like "Teferi, Time Raveler" and "Consing to Memory" provide additional disruption and card advantage, while powerful threats like "Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer" and "Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury" can quickly close out the game. The deck aims to be proactive and disruptive, making it difficult for the opponent to execute their game plan effectively.

The deck revolves around generating mana quickly through rituals and medallions to cast spells like Ral, Monsoon Mage and Glimpse the Impossible, ultimately leading to a powerful combo finish with cards like Grapeshot. The deck aims to chain spells together efficiently, utilizing cards like Reckless Impulse and Manamorphose to dig through the deck and find combo pieces. The inclusion of Past in Flames allows for spells to be cast from the graveyard, ensuring the combo can be executed even if key pieces are countered or removed.

The deck focuses on aggressive play with a mix of creatures and spells to quickly deal damage to the opponent. It utilizes cards like Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer to apply early pressure, while also including removal spells like Galvanic Discharge and Thraben Charm to control the board. Ajani, Nacatl Pariah provides additional aggression and synergy with the creature base. The deck also incorporates disruptive elements like Blood Moon and Static Prison to hinder opponents' strategies, making it a fast-paced and versatile aggro deck in the Modern format.

The deck focuses on controlling the opponent's resources through a combination of counter spells, hand disruption, and removal spells. It aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan with cards like Thoughtseize and Force of Negation, while also utilizing cards like Fatal Push and Cling to Dust to deal with threats on the board. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student and Quantum Riddler provide card advantage and filtering, while Murktide Regent and Psychic Frog offer win conditions. The deck aims to out value and out tempo the opponent, ultimately grinding them out for a victory.

The main strategy of this deck is to use disruptive creatures and control spells to slow down the opponent while also applying aggressive pressure with efficient creatures like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd. Teferi, Time Raveler helps to protect the board and disrupt the opponent's game plan. Consign to Memory provides card advantage and removal, while Fable of the Mirror-Breaker can generate additional value. Prismatic Ending and Solitude offer versatile removal options. Quantum Riddler and Phlage, Titan of Fire's Fury provide additional threats to close out the game quickly. The mana base allows for consistent casting of spells while still enabling powerful plays.

This deck utilizes a fast mana package alongside card draw and card filtering to generate a large amount of mana quickly. Combining spells that offer card selection and graveyard recursion with powerful storm payoff cards, this deck aims to cast a high storm count spell such as Grapeshot to deal lethal damage to the opponent. The deck maximizes efficiency by reducing the cost of red spells with Ruby Medallion and utilizing Ral, Monsoon Mage for additional card advantage and removal. The deck also includes a Wish sideboard package to provide additional flexibility and options.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan with disruptive creatures and control elements while also applying pressure with aggressive threats. By utilizing cards that can disrupt the opponent's spells and permanents, along with creatures that can provide card advantage and evasion, the deck aims to control the game's tempo and win through incremental advantage. The deck also includes removal spells to deal with threats and maintain board control. Overall, the strategy is to disrupt the opponent's resources while applying pressure to win the game efficiently.

The deck focuses on generating +1/+1 counters on creatures and using them to take advantage of various synergies and combo interactions. It relies on cards like Blade of the Bloodchief and Grist, the Hunger Tide to grow your creatures, while using cards like Walking Ballista and Malevolent Rumble to control the board. Additionally, it includes recursion effects like Dredger's Insight and Wall of Roots to ensure a steady stream of resources. The goal is to overwhelm your opponent with a powerful army of creatures that can quickly close out the game.

The deck focuses on using instant reanimation spells like Goryo's Vengeance and Ephemerate to quickly bring back powerful creatures like Griselbrand and Atraxa, Grand Unifier from the graveyard. It also includes disruptive spells like Thoughtseize and Force of Negation to control the opponent's strategy. The deck aims to quickly assemble the necessary combo pieces to overwhelm the opponent and secure victory with a combination of card advantage, powerful creatures, and disruption. The key strategy is to efficiently reanimate threats while disrupting the opponent's game plan.

The deck focuses on playing aggressively to deal damage quickly to the opponent. It utilizes aggressive creatures such as Monastery Swiftspear and Dragon's Rage Channeler, along with burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart to control the board and go face. The deck also includes card draw and selection spells like Preordain and Expressive Iteration to maintain a constant flow of threats. Overall, the strategy is to apply pressure early and maintain it throughout the game, aiming to finish off the opponent before they can stabilize.

The deck revolves around assembling a combo using cards like Broodscale, Blade of the Bloodchief, and Glaring Fleshraker to generate massive amounts of value and overwhelm the opponent. It also utilizes disruption and control elements such as Kozilek's Command and Malevolent Rumble to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck aims to set up a powerful board presence quickly and efficiently, while also having answers to threats from the opponent. The addition of Eldrazi creatures like Emrakul, the Promised End provides additional win conditions and adds variety to the strategy.

The main focus of this deck is to quickly deploy threat creatures like Dragon's Rage Channeler and Monastery Swiftspear, while using cheap spells like Mutagenic Growth and Lightning Bolt to remove opponent's creatures or push through damage. The deck aims to have a fast and aggressive start, utilizing burn spells and evasion abilities to maximize damage output. In addition, cards like Mishra's Bauble and Expressive Iteration provide card selection and advantage, ensuring a consistent flow of threats and answers. The mana base is streamlined for efficiency and consistency in casting spells and deploying threats.

The deck focuses on quickly playing low-cost artifacts to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and disruptive spells, while utilizing cards like Engineered Explosives and Tormod's Crypt to control the board. The deck also includes artifacts like Mox Opal and Mishra's Bauble to ramp up mana and draw cards, as well as lands like Urza's Saga to search for key artifacts. This aggressive strategy is supported by a mix of direct damage spells like Galvanic Blast and equipment like Shadowspear to push through damage and deal with threats efficiently.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly and aggressively deal damage to your opponent using efficient spells like Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart, along with creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Dragon's Rage Channeler. The deck also includes cards like Mutagenic Growth and Violent Urge to increase damage output and enhance the aggressiveness of your creatures. Close out games by overwhelming your opponent with quick, efficient creatures and direct damage spells. Use card filtering and advantage from cards like Expressive Iteration and Mishra's Bauble to maintain momentum and stay ahead in the game.
